sections.description: Initial Access consists of techniques that use various entry vectors to gain their initial foothold within a network.
sections.name: 1. Initial Access Remediation

sections.description: Execution consists of techniques that result in adversary-controlled code running on a local or remote system.
sections.name: 2. Execution Remediation

sections.description: Credential Access consists of techniques for stealing credentials like account names and passwords.
sections.name: 6. Credential Access Remediation

sections.description: Defense Evasion consists of techniques that adversaries use to avoid detection throughout their compromise.
sections.name: 5. Defense Evasion Remediation

sections.description: Collection consists of techniques adversaries may use to gather information and the sources information is collected from that are relevant to following through on the adversaryâ€™s objectives.
sections.name: 9. Collection Remediation

sections.description: Persistence consists of techniques that adversaries use to keep access to systems across restarts, changed credentials, and other interruptions that could cut off their access.
sections.name: 3. Persistence Remediation

sections.description: Lateral Movement consists of techniques that adversaries use to enter and control remote systems on a network.
sections.name: 8. Lateral Movement Remediation

sections.description: Discovery consists of techniques an adversary may use to gain knowledge about the system and internal network.
sections.name: 7. Discovery Remediation

sections.description: Privilege Escalation consists of techniques that adversaries use to gain higher-level permissions on a system or network.
sections.name: 4. Privilege Escalation Remediation

sections.description: Impact consists of techniques that adversaries use to disrupt availability or compromise integrity by manipulating business and operational processes.
sections.name: 12. Impact Remediation

sections.description: Exfiltration consists of techniques that adversaries may use to steal data from your network.
sections.name: 11. Exfiltration Remediation

sections.description: Command and Control consists of techniques that adversaries may use to communicate with systems under their control within a victim network.
sections.name: 10. Command and Control Remediation
